      </div>
      <p style="font-size:11px;color:#f15b5c;background:rgba(241,91,92,0.06);border-radius:6px;padding:8px 12px;margin:0;">⚑ Note: Deep Navy #025870 is not in the official brand kit. Dr. Z will need to decide whether to adopt it as a brand extension or stay strictly within the original palette.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="compare-grid">
      <div class="col-a">
        <p class="col-title">Version A — Official Brand Colors</p>
        <p style="font-size:11px;font-weight:600;color:#555;margin:0 0 8px;">Strengths</p>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot pro-dot-a"></div><p>Bold and energetic — immediately eye-catching on an ad or social feed</p></div>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot pro-dot-a"></div><p>100% on-brand — uses only approved hex codes from the brand kit</p></div>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot pro-dot-a"></div><p>Coral as a hero color signals urgency and emotion — works well for a conversion page</p></div>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot pro-dot-a"></div><p>High contrast — accessible and readable on mobile</p></div>
        <p style="font-size:11px;font-weight:600;color:#555;margin:10px 0 8px;">Considerations</p>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot con-dot"></div><p>Coral as a dominant background can feel alarming in a health context — red-adjacent colors often signal danger</p></div>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot con-dot"></div><p>Less premium feel — may read more like a consumer app than a clinical health tool</p></div>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot con-dot"></div><p>When everything is coral, the CTA button loses its punch — nothing stands out</p></div>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot con-dot"></div><p>Yellow nav bar on coral background creates visual noise</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-b">
        <p class="col-title">Version B — Deep Navy System ★ Recommended</p>
        <p style="font-size:11px;font-weight:600;color:#555;margin:0 0 8px;">Strengths</p>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot pro-dot-b"></div><p>Premium and trustworthy — navy reads as authoritative and calm, ideal for health</p></div>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot pro-dot-b"></div><p>Coral CTA pops dramatically against navy — the most important button is impossible to miss</p></div>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot pro-dot-b"></div><p>Gold accents create warmth without overwhelming — feels human and approachable</p></div>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot pro-dot-b"></div><p>Teal used subtly as a supporting tone — all three brand colors still present</p></div>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot pro-dot-b"></div><p>Aligns with the About page voice — "calm authority, no hype"</p></div>
        <p style="font-size:11px;font-weight:600;color:#555;margin:10px 0 8px;">Considerations</p>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot con-dot"></div><p>#025870 is not in the official brand kit — requires Dr. Z's approval to adopt</p></div>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot con-dot"></div><p>Less immediately attention-grabbing in a social ad context than coral</p></div>
        <div class="pro"><div class="pro-dot con-dot"></div><p>Darker palette may need careful attention to accessibility on mobile screens in bright light</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rec-box">
      <h3>Our recommendation</h3>
      <p>Version B — the deep navy system — is the stronger design direction for DiagnoseThis. The brand's own About page describes the tone as "calm authority, no hype, clean and minimal." Navy delivers that. Coral as a background feels energetic for ads but undermines trust in a logged-in health experience where users are sharing sensitive symptoms.</p>
      <p>The practical solution: <strong style="color:#FFB533;">use Coral for ads and landing page CTAs</strong> (where boldness converts) and <strong style="color:#FFB533;">use Navy as the app's primary background</strong> (where trust and clarity matter). This gives Dr. Z both — energy for acquisition, authority for retention.</p>
      <p class="note">⚑ Dr. Z will need to formally approve #025870 as a brand color extension, or provide an alternative dark anchor color from the official palette.</p>
